    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-06-06T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-06-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">886D.2553/6–651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GWS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d126fn1">Repeated to Basra.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-06-06T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 6, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6402. Gulf reps told us last night that when they went around to see <gloss
                        target="#t_AIOC1">AIOC</gloss> yesterday to sign agreement on principles of
                    plan to increase Kuwait’s oil revenues (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 6374, June 5),<note n="2" xml:id="d126fn2">Not
                        printed.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_JB1">Jackson</persName> told them that he was sorry that
                    he was unable to sign. He vaguely mentioned necessity <pb facs="0358" n="318"
                        xml:id="pg_318"/> putting draft agreement to company’s fin comite on July
                    14, but Gulf reps were unable to get any clear explanation as to why <persName
                        corresp="#p_JB1">Jackson</persName> unable sign agreement then and there.
                        <persName corresp="#p_JB1">Jackson</persName> did, however, state that he
                    regarded document as agreed but just was not able sign it then.</p>
                <p>Moreover, mtg with <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>, which <persName
                        corresp="#p_BVS1">Victor Butler</persName> was arranging, did not take place
                    yesterday and Gulf has not yet been able ascertain reasons therefor or determine
                    whether mtg will be arranged later.</p>
                <p>Until inland revenue has formulated its position (which shld be in next few days)
                    and we know its precise nature, it is difficult for us to take further
                        steps.<note n="3" xml:id="d126fn3">Telegram 6568 from London, June 14,
                        reported the British Department of Inland Revenue might not insist on
                        knowing the position of the U.S. Treasury regarding the eligibility of an
                            <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss>-type tax for credit against
                        U.S. taxes before it decided on the Kuwait case. The Ambassador, however,
                        thought it would help to expedite the British decision if the Department of
                        State could obtain a Treasury ruling or inform the British that it was not
                        possible to obtain a Treasury ruling prior to an audit of the tax returns.
                        (886D.2553/6–1451)</note> We have, however, spoken to <persName
                        corresp="#p_FHTN1">Gaitskell</persName>, who has promised to look into
                    matter, and are keeping in close touch with <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_Min1">Min</gloss> Fuel and Power.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GWS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
